{"title":"LogicInsight - Nutanix Hosts Overview","description":"### **📊 LogicInsight - Nutanix Hosts Overview Dashboard Explanation**\n\nThe **LogicInsight - Nutanix Hosts Overview Dashboard** provides a **comprehensive view of all Nutanix cluster hosts**, helping administrators monitor **host performance, capacity, and resource usage**. It includes **real-time metrics on CPU, memory, storage, and I/O operations**, ensuring optimal cluster health and performance.\n\n***\n\n## **1️⃣ Hosts Summary (Green Section - Left)**\n\nThis section provides an **overview of host status and capacity**:\n\n-   **Hosts Degraded** – Displays the number of hosts experiencing failures or hardware issues.\n\n-   **Hosts In Maintenance** – Shows how many hosts are currently under maintenance.\n\n-   **Hosts Number Pie Chart** – Displays the distribution of hosts among different clusters.\n\n-   **Capacity Table:**\n\n    -   Provides key information about each host, including:\n\n        -   **Memory (RAM)**\n        -   **Number of CPU Cores & Sockets**\n        -   **CPU Frequency**\n        -   **Total Storage Capacity**\n        -   **vCPU Ratio (virtual CPUs per physical core)**\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nThis section allows administrators to **quickly check host health and resource distribution across clusters**.\n\n***\n\n## **2️⃣ Host Resource Monitoring (Yellow Section - Middle)**\n\nThis section tracks **storage and CPU resource usage per host**:\n\n-   **Free Storage vs. Usage (1 day) Chart:**\n\n    -   Compares available storage space to used storage over the past 24 hours.\n    -   Highlights potential **storage shortages** or imbalances.\n\n-   **CPU Usage % Pie Chart:**\n\n    -   Displays CPU utilization across different hosts.\n    -   Helps identify if any host is **overloaded or underutilized**.\n\n-   **Memory Usage % Pie Chart:**\n\n    -   Shows how much RAM is being consumed per host.\n    -   Ensures **memory is allocated efficiently across the cluster**.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nThese metrics **help prevent performance bottlenecks by identifying hosts with high CPU or memory utilization**.\n\n***\n\n## **3️⃣ Hosts Performance (Purple Section - Right)**\n\nThis section provides **detailed host performance metrics**:\n\n-   **CPU Usage Chart:**\n\n    -   Displays real-time **CPU usage trends across all hosts**.\n    -   High spikes indicate **potential performance bottlenecks**.\n\n-   **Memory Usage Chart:**\n\n    -   Monitors memory consumption across hosts.\n    -   Ensures that **memory allocation is balanced** across the cluster.\n\n-   **Disk IOPS Chart:**\n\n    -   Tracks **Input/Output Operations Per Second (IOPS)** on each host’s storage.\n    -   High IOPS means **intensive disk activity**, which may impact performance.\n\n-   **Disk IO Bandwidth Chart:**\n\n    -   Measures **how much data is being read/written per second**.\n    -   Helps detect **storage bottlenecks and workload imbalance**.\n\n-   **Disk Avg IO Latency Chart:**\n\n    -   Shows **how long storage operations take to complete**.\n    -   High latency can indicate **storage performance issues**.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nThis section **ensures that CPU, memory, and storage performance remain stable**, preventing **resource contention or failures**.\n\n***\n\n### **📌 Why This Dashboard Matters?**\n\n✅ **Detect Host Failures Early** – Quickly identify degraded or overloaded hosts.\\\n✅ **Optimize Resource Allocation** – Ensure CPU, memory, and storage are evenly distributed.\\\n✅ **Monitor Performance Trends** – Track historical usage to plan for scaling.\\\n✅ **Prevent Downtime** – Identify issues before they impact applications and workloads.","widgets":[{"id":2755879321490856,"definition":{"type":"image","url":"https://logicappupdate.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dash_logo.png","sizing":"cover","has_background":true,"has_border":true,"vertical_align":"center","horizontal_align":"center"},"layout":{"x":0,"y":0,"width":6,"height"